Commit: cdf860ac270e9c1137d55aa32e072bef873568d6 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg], [ASL]

  [WWAN] Accessing PCI configure space via ECAM in ACPI OpRegion
  
  Merging a531db5f888aa27a24e1467c7758f69b639b060e from WHL to ICL.
  For some scenarios, accessing PCI config space through I/O may not be
  allowed by Windows and leads to some unexpected issues in WWAN RTD3.
  Changed WWAN root port OperationRegion from PCI_Config to SystemMemory
  to avoid the issue.
  
  Hsd-es-id: 1607648178
  Change-Id: Ic891e9835fb93c3a53bf2a4b151aeb5e87c04c89
  Original commit hash: 0a48245a5e3b599c8fb22a7724d9d2c1a44627e8

*********************************************************************************
Commit: a7843aed2003c45aa2382b1f5753dd1d224e661d 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL][MRC] Read Timing Centering Optimization and RxV degradation enhancements
  Add the following changes to MrcReadTimingCenteringOpt():
  - check if optimization is needed: if we have enough RdT margin then optimization not needed.
  - Add margin RdV check on timing 0, instead of get it from previous RMT - get better results
  - Run The Read Timing Centering Opimization after the Round Trip Latency Step -it resolves the degradation of 2-3 ticks in RxV.
  Additional changes:
  - fix bug in CaFindEdge() - Status need to be cleared inside per channel loop
  - Update Ron / ODT comp targets in CalcStaticDynamicLegSize() - they should be multiplied by number of segments
  Change-Id: I0ea54ea975aa55e18ad2c96fd86accb72525e1c4
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcStartMemoryConfiguration.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 06e125b9f61b932bf84c5200061db901ee61fb27 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg], [SA], [MRC]

  Description: Not able to protect whole DMA region with PMR
  [Platfrom Change]
  1) Changed PMR coverage region: PLMR = 0 to (IMR - DMA buffer), PHMR = 4G to TOUUD
  2) Moved the VTD driver call back to End of PEI to allign with EDK2 and FSP boot flow
  3) Force re-boot DMA protection enable for the first boot after flash
  [EDK2 change]
  1) IOMMU PMR feature should be generic to support different hardware
  architecture. Platforms may request no overlap between PMR regions
  and system reserve memory. Create an interface to control PLMR/PHMR
  regions. It allows silicon code to adjust PLMR/PHMR region base on
  the project needs.
  2) DisableDMAr Function Code Optimization
  3) Renamed InitDmar() to InitGlobalVtd()
  4) A new GetVtdPmrAlignmentLib for silicon code to get
  PMR alignment values.
  Change-Id: If97298b9710a6455adb4ab0ff1dc8a4ed269c409
  
  
  IceLakeFspPkg/IceLakeFspPkg.dsc
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Features/VTd/IntelVTdPmrPei/IntelVTdPmrPei.uni

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 1e1b023181bf70fe52590bd306be50635fa4cc7e 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg]

  ICL Security [Harmonized Capsule] : SUT hangs at PC 10B4  on giving power interrupt while Capsule is updating via harmonized Monolithic Capsule.
  Current FW component update order is ME->PDT->BIOS->EC.
  When ME update is interrupted, ME would go into Recovery mode. In Me Recovery mode, the interface to ISH PDT is not supported.
  This causes the following PDT update issue when system is continuing form an interrupted ME FW update.
  Change the update order to update PDT first then ME.
  Change-Id: Iae887c106ef1b56418c5f7974fda446a96240040
  
  
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Features/CapsuleUpdate/Library/FmpDeviceLibMonolithic/FmpDeviceLib.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 609776a99c2ad1004d56186f9e96422a3b06f627 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg]

  [ICL] Need to cherry pick broken SMBIOS table fix (specific HW configuration)
  SMBIOS Type1 information was corrupted after Windows restart. During getting Type1 serial number, BIOS ignores incorrect data from I2C chip and populated the field with incorrect data. This makes Windows abort filling BIOS information registry key.
  Resolution: 1. Corrected System information I2C chip detection. Some macro defintions were incorrectly defiened.
  2. Added a check to see if the extracted Serial Number contains a valid data. If no data, BIOS now skipps Type1/2 Serial number update process.
  Change-Id: I9b7ff019e8a31897759e02d319b413a597015eee
  
  
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Features/Smbios/SmbiosMiscDxe/SmbiosMiscEntryPoint.c
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Include/Library/PssLib.h
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Library/PssLib/PssLib.c

  [ICL MRC][Need to limit the speed at Gear1 according to Max_Data_Rate_At_GEAR1 fuse]

Commit: c13c6c566166401fe9d82a9e99b3cd158ab89b78 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL-U SDS][ICL-YN][ICL-Y][CI Build- SUT is not booting with release BIOS hang @ PC-0080]
  Issue:
  Some ICL parts fail ERDTC2D step at LPDDR4-3200 sporadically, only in Release BIOS build.
  Root cause:
  JWL FlyBy algorithm has an "early exit" feature where we break from the DqOffset loop once all bytes have passed.
  This is only done when debug prints are disabled, hence only Release build failed.
  Solution:
  With the current usage model we need go over all DqOffset values, to properly do the early Tx DqDqs centering in JWL FlyBy.
  Additional changes:
  - Double the Gear2 ReadMPR range for LP4, to be the same as DDR4. This allows better early Rx DqDqs centering.
  - Moved ERDTC2D back to before RDVC1D.
  - Remove Early WrV at the end of JWL FlyBy, it's not needed if we run EWRTC2D after this step.
  - Added "_BIOSVER_" signature right before MRC Version so that it can be easily located in BIOS ROM file.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/Include/MrcInterface.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/MemoryInit.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcGeneral.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcSaveRestore.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcStartMemoryConfiguration.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/ReadTraining/MrcReadDqDqs.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcCommon.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/WriteTraining/MrcWriteLeveling.c

Commit: ca67e2ad9b7c60378c3b654cd663ea6b0e0ac23f 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL MRC][Move ERDTC2D before EWRTC2D]
  Issue:
  Fix fail in EWRTC2D step at LPDDR4-3733.
  Root cause:
  Insufficient RD margins after ReadMPR cause early write centering to fail.
  Solution:
  Move ERDTC2D before EWRTC2D, right after JWL FlyBy step.
  Update JWL FlyBy to keep TxDq centered per byte.
  Run early WrV centering at the end of JWL FlyBy using same stress as in JWL FlyBy.
  Additional change:
  - Fix CPGC Chunk Error reporting and add it to DQTimeCentering1D routine.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/Include/MrcInterface.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcStartMemoryConfiguration.c

[SA], [MRC]

  [Nanya NT6AP256T32AV-J2  LPDDR4x can't boot at  3733 on ICL-U]
  Issue:
  MRC fails in basic training at high speed LP4/x due to wrong initial CmdV setting.
  Solution:
  Added new training step - Early Command Voltage Centering.
  This should run on LP4 at high speeds (above 2400), right after ECT.
  It uses MPR stress to center CmdV.
  Additional changes:
  - Change LP4X initial Cmd Ron target from 20 to 30 Ohm
  - Repeat each point test 10 times during CA training in ECT.
  - Remove CmdVoltageCenteringPreLCT - it's no longer needed.
  - Added Nanya to SMBIOS table strings list

*********************************************************************************
Commit: dc230cafca05b31ac6e1ff66169b847ae847d300 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL MRC][CmdVC1D - inconsistent pass / fail report during CAVref sweep on LP4/X]
  Issue:
  During CMDVC1D step on LP4/X we see false pass regions in the failing range, sporadically.
  Root cause:
  When MRC changes CA Vref, we program FSP[1] while being at FSP[1].
  Solution:
  Program CA Vref from FSP[0] point, similar to JEDEC Init flow:
  - Set MR13 FSP_WR=1, FSP_OP = 0
  - Switch to 1067/G1
  - Issue MRW's to MR12 to set CaVref code/range in FSP[1]
  - Switch back to FSP_OP=1, and High Frequency
  Keep CKE Low during frequency change.
  Additional change:
  - Update PU-Cal SOC ODT table to match JEDEC spec.
  - Fix delays in Pcode mailbox routines in MiniBios
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/MemoryTypes/MrcLpddr4.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcCommon.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/MiniBios/MEMORY/MrcOemPlatform.c

Commit: 685134bb621ab1e8ee7a3ff1ae729034553063cf 
*********************************************************************************

[SA], [ASL]

  Description: BIOS should not use Current HPD Indicator bit (Mailbox 1, offset 0xA8) which is Obsolete as per latest ACPI Opregion spec
  Solution: ICL driver does not report Current HPD Indicator bit (Mailbox 1, offset 0xA8) to BIOS.? This is not valid for LFPs and modern OSes.
  Change is to be done in BIOS to not use this field and not send additional ACPI notification - EventType = ACPI; Event = 0(Unknown); Argument = NULL to OS, if this bit is not set.
  Impacted Platform: ICL
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/AcpiTables/SaSsdt/IgfxCommon.asl

Commit: 8d1f77a25807773eb8495fb36101f169857ef699 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg]

  SecurityPkg/TcgConfigDxe: Allow enabling TPM 1.2 device from disabled state.
  Pull from b49758c11280a0dfba981632ed6ed06ed80a30d8 of EDKII master.
  Currently the TCG config setup form defaults the physical presence action to
  PHYSICAL_PRESENCE_ENABLE, this prevents the action from being called. When a TPM
  1.2 device is in Disabled and Activated state it is not possible to issue the
  PHYSICAL_PRESENCE_ENABLE using the menu action.
  By having the form default to PHYSICAL_PRESENCE_NO_ACTION, the user is now able
  to select PHYSICAL_PRESENCE_ENABLE and toggle the TPM 1.2 device enable state.
  
  
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Override/DoxygenRpOverride.md
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Override/SecurityPkg/Tcg/TcgConfigDxe/TcgConfig.vfr
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Override/SecurityPkg/Tcg/TcgConfigDxe/TcgConfigDriver.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 5263e0db5b8d7545199c1606ad0bfab83e489a1a 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg], [MRC]

  [ICL MRC][Limit non-respin LP4 boards to 3200]
  Issue:
  Current MRC will enable LP4-3733 on D-step and up, on all LP4 boards, regardless of FAB ID (before DDR re-spin and after re-spin).
  Solution:
  MRC should limit the LP4 speed to 3200 on old boards (before re-spin), using default SPD image.
  additional change;
  Enable LPDDR4 in D0 step and above to 3733 (as LP4X) on spinned boards
  Board   ID          Non-respin                              Respin              NOTE
  =====   ==          ==========                              ======              ====
  ICL-Y   0x16/0x17   FAB_ID = 0, 1, 2                        FAB_ID = 3          BOM_ID = 4: LP4x
  ICL-U   0x09        FAB_ID = 0                              FAB_ID = 1          BOM_ID = 4: LP4x
  ICL-YN  0x18        FAB_ID = 0                              FAB_ID = 1          LP4x only
  ICL-UN  0x19        FAB_ID = 0                              FAB_ID = 1          LP4x only
  SDS     0x0C        FAB_ID = 0, 1: LP4; FAB_ID=2: LP4X      FAB_ID = 3 (LP4x)
  
  
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Board/Others/PeiBoardInitLib/BoardSaInitPreMemLib.c
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Include/PlatformBoardId.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/Library/PeiSaPolicyLib/MrcOemPlatform.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/Include/MrcInterface.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcGeneral.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 11a60611288a5aa3d583040832b844cf4fc9f37c 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL MRC][ForceBiasOn and ForceRxOn are left enabled at the end of SOT training]
  Issue:
  High VDDQ power consumption observed after MRC 0.0.4.40
  Root Cause:
  MRC 0.0.4.40 adds a second call to SOT training, after Read Equalization or Read Amplifier Power steps.
  SOT step enables ForceBiasOn and ForceRxOn, and does not clear them at the end.
  When SOT was called only at the beginning of MRC, this was not causing issues because these knobs are disabled in a later basic training steps.
  But when SOT is called after Power training steps, these knobs stay enabled.
  Solution:
  Save ForceBiasOn and ForceRxOn at the beginning of SOT training, and restore them at the end.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcCrosser.c
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Potential Errors Below:

  --Commit Message Contains Key Word: step

*********************************************************************************
Commit: ed5dded25b9951e873612be70918f110e4a9ea7d 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL U] [LP4x][Micron Byte mode drams MT53E2G32D8QD-046 WT:E fail At MRC activate]
  Issue:
  MRC is not following latest JEDEC LP4 SPD spec update for Byte Mode detection in Byte 12 bit [6].
  Solution:
  Update MRC to use Byte 12 bit [6] for Byte Mode detection instead of bits [2:0] - DeviceWidth.
  Support existing SPD images by detecting Byte Mode also if DeviceWidth is 8, regardless of byte 12 bit [6].
  Examples:
  DeviceWidth = 8  and bit[6] = 0 -- means byte mode (old / current SPD images)
  DeviceWidth = 16 and bit[6] = 1 -- also means byte mode (new SPD images)
  Additional changes:
  - Renamed DimmOut->ChannelsPerSdramPackage to ChannelsPerDie, as this is how we use it in MRC.
  - Added Nanya MR5 and JEDEC IDs
  - Updated TC automation script to support 'ICLBranch' instead of 'master'
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/Include/MrcInterface.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/Include/MrcSpdData.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcApi.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcGeneral.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 6c91c232fe394caff89901bc487739d2ef03f29f 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg], [TBT]

  [TCSS] Adjust TPL level of DisableITbtBmeCallBackFunction in the ITbtDxe.c
  The UEFI XHCI codes are different between AMI and Intel BIOS. AMI implemented USB codes that register callback function at the ExitBootServices event by using TPL_NOTIFY as well.
  Root cause is AMI Usb module stops the usb devices and controllers at the ExitBootServices event by using TPL_NOTIFY and ITbtDisableBmeCallBackFunction is triggered at the ExitBootServices event using TPL_NOTIFY as well. If ITbtDisableBmeCallBackFunction run firstly, Intel disables BME bit, then USB can't send any comments to Usb devices to stop them by AMI xHCI driver. This is an event executed sequence problem.
  
  
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Features/Tbt/TbtInit/Dxe/DTbtDxe.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Tbt/ITbtInit/Dxe/ITbtDxe.c
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Commit: a794fbdd2a639e9af91c0c9d17063d22a8cb3fe8 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg]

  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/CapsuleUpdate: When FW is in recovery mode platform does not boot
  Problem:
  1. ME FWU API FwuGetIshPdtVersion() is invoked to report PDT version info of ISH PDT FMP during POST.
  2. SVME or CSME in Recovery mode does not support the HECI commands in FwuGetIshPdtVersion()
  Solution:
  1. Deprecating PDT version string reporting as of now since reporting a version which is always fixed does not have much value.
  This should resolve system hanging/delay issue on both SV ME and regular CSME in Recovery mode during POST.
  (If PDT version is more meaningful in the future and is planned to be reported in PDT FMP, we can apply the same condition check described below.)
  2. Adding ME mode/status check before updating PDT in FmpDeviceSetImage(), system only proceeds the PDT update when ME is in Normal Mode with ME_READY status.

*********************************************************************************
Commit: a4d7b7bd99ed83e6250ae1401d768f0998fda9c1 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL MRC][DataControl2.ForceBiasOn is set on LPDDR4]
  Issue:
  DataControl2.ForceBiasOn is set on LPDDR4, this causes extra power consumption.
  Root cause:
  It is set at the end of JWL FlyBy for QCLK greater than 1333, which is supposed to be for DDR4 only, but it's set on LP4 as well.
  Solution:
  Clear ForceBiasOn on LP4 at the end of JWL FlyBy step.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/WriteTraining/MrcWriteLeveling.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 79a04cde8bc26295ea1d8303a97e3e5c99ac924f 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL MRC][RxRankMuxDelay is too small in Gear2]
  Issue:
  Sporadic memory failures after MRC using specific Hynix DDR4 DIMMs at 3200.
  Root cause:
  RxRankMuxDelay is too short in Gear2.
  tRDRD_dr turnaround is too short with some 2R DIMMs.
  Solution:
  Add +1 to the RxRankMuxDelay Gear2 formula, this also aligns it with AV code.
  Increase tRDRD_dr from 6 to 8 in DDR4 / Gear2.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Hal/MrcHalRegisterAccess.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/McConfiguration/MrcTimingConfiguration.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: b911fb7d6479fa4ee63d7c8f40daa2f478d73b0a 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL MRC][LP4 Read Leveling fails in Step 1]
  Issue:
  1. Read Leveling fails sporadically on LP4 at high speeds (3733+), where width of strobe in Step 1 is 24 ticks, versus ideal 64 ticks.
  2. In LP4 SOT training stage 2, the DQS is always zero.
  Root cause:
  1. DataControl0.EarlyRLeakEn was not set
  2. Park mode / Leaker was not disabled in SOT step
  Solution:
  1. Set DataControl0.EarlyRLeakEn, and LeakerComp to 2.
  2. Set RxDqsAmpOffset to 0 during Read Leveling step to ensure better internal DQS sampling with RecvEn.
  - Keep it zero at the end of the step, lab data shows that this improves Rx margins.
  3. Disable Park mode / Leaker in SOT step
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcInterpreter.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Hal/MrcHalRegisterAccess.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/ReadTraining/MrcReadReceiveEnable.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcCrosser.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcMcConfiguration.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/MiniBios/MEMORY/MrcOemPlatform.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 9c9fbec34dc7a0fc33449fa58eae7d0d0995dff2 
*********************************************************************************


  BpCommonPkg/HddPassword: Enable Freeze Lock feature.
  ATA command has an command named Freeze Lock which used to
  lock the device. After this action, all security command
  send to the device will be ignored by the device. It's an
  security feature used to control the device.
  Current HddPassword driver not enables this feature. It may
  cause HDD device been locked by third party software. This
  is an unexpected behavior. This patch enables freeze lock
  feature for HddPassword solution.
  
  
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword2/AhciMode.c
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword2/AhciMode.h
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword2/HddPassword.vfr
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword2/HddPassword2Dxe.c
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword2/HddPassword2Dxe.h
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword2/HddPassword2Pei.c
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword2/HddPassword2Pei.h

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 07eec151dccbda4f1f92377b912c0ca70e0c4c66 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg], [ASL], [SA]

  Description: [TCSS][RTD3]System hangs at B503/B504 CATERROR (Reset_Prep) during S3/S4 Entry with Akitio attached sporadically because of PCIe not responding
  Solution: Enable iTBT RTD3 setup option in BIOS by default
  1. Remove DLSULPPGA per upcoming BWG change.
  2. De-optimize polling loop to exclude compiler optimization concern
  3. Adjust timeout to 100 ms for each polling, interval is 5 ms.
  4. Propagate Sx decision by _DSW of DMA. [Restriction: if there is no TBT enabled, then the SD3C will always be 0 and _OFF method of D3C PowerResource will always put TCSS to TC Cold]
  5. Enable ITBT RTD3 by default for ICL U/Y Bx stepping
  6. Add restriction to TCCold to depend on TBT IP.

*********************************************************************************
Commit: b78b06a6b8c02834c5fa59d3330394fccdaaabb9 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL MRC][CmdVC1D - inconsistent pass / fail report during CAVref sweep on LP4/X]
  Issue:
  During CMDVC1D step on LP4/X we see false pass regions in the failing range, sporadically.
  Root cause:
  When MRC changes CA Vref, we program FSP[1] while being at FSP[1].
  Solution:
  Program CA Vref from FSP[0] point, similar to JEDEC Init flow:
  - Set MR13 FSP_WR=1, FSP_OP = 0
  - Switch to 1067/G1
  - Issue MRW's to MR12 to set CaVref code/range in FSP[1]
  - Switch back to FSP_OP=1, and High Frequency
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/MemoryTypes/MrcLpddr4.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcCommon.c

  --Commit Message Contains Key Word: step

[MRC]

  [ICL MRC][MRC changes from EV branch]
  MRC changes from EV branch:
  1. MrcGetUpmPwrLimit - double the RxT UPM/PWR limits in Gear2
  2. Move MrcEarlyReadTimingCentering2D step before MrcReadVoltageCentering, currently it runs after it and hurts RdV margins.
  3. DDR4 RMT: fix a bug where Rank1 CmdV results were stored in Rank0 in MarginResult, causing RMT to show zero CmdV margins on R1
  Additional fix:
  - PowerTrainingMode override to margin or power mode was done using Outputs->FreqMax instead of Outputs->Frequency.

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 427ea80e64147851cf810bfa3c6705c457d347f9 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL-U2][B2][DDR4][MRC 3.149][PMO failures][Cold Boot cycles failure at normal mode]
  Issue:
  MRC fails in Normal Mode memtest or in BIOS after MRC, at 2667/G2, with particular DDR4 DIMMs, for example:
  HMAA4GS6MJR8N-XN N0 AD [32GB 2Rx8 3200]
  Root Cause:
  RxFIFO read enable flyby (RxDqFifoRdEnRank) was programmed incorrectly.
  This happened because MRC was programming it in UI units instead of tCK units.
  Also the layout of the register in G2 is such that bit [0] should not be used.
  Solution:
  1. Change the logic in Read Leveling and RT Latency optimization steps to program RxDqFifoRdEnRank in tCK units in G2.
  2. In G2 program the RxDqFifoRdEnRank value in bits [3:1] of the register field, keeping bit [0] as zero.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcGeneral.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Hal/MrcHalRegisterAccess.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/ReadTraining/MrcReadReceiveEnable.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/MiniBios/MEMORY/MrcSetup.c

Commit: 91b53042090248a20049d6c16863f0284f80cb11

[PlatformPkg]

  ICL_security[ICL U /Y] :PTT is not enumerating in OS with Release BIOS 2482.02
  This regression result from commit cc9702ac7a0db8e66eefbd8ba1cb7e043a52b9e7.
  1. The value of PcdCRBIdleByPass should be decided based on hardware readiness of PTP 1.03 spec insdead of BootMode.
  We should keep its value as 0xFF (default value) before complete PTP 1.03 support is in place.
  2. Skip GoIdle request when BootMode is not BOOT_ON_S3_RESUME.

*********************************************************************************
Commit: e1a701554c5c5ce50852e0e71b230656617f2d40 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg]

  Install RstLegacyBootDisabledProtocol
  RST UEFI driver can't be allowed to load on the systems
  where legacy RST driver is supposed to be supported.
  To achieve it RST UEFI driver dispatch has been made to depend
  on the RstLegacyBootDisabledProtocol presence. The reason why
  RST can't be allowed to dispatch is that after software remapping
  support has been added a discrepancy between Supported and Start call
  in DriverBindingProtocol has been created. This discrepancy is causing
  NVMe drives that could be software remapped to not be enumerated if legacy
  boot is enabled.
  New driver has been added to install this dependency. In
  the future all dependencies for RST driver should
  be handled by this additional driver.
  
  
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Features/Rst/RstUefiDriverSupport/RstUefiDriverSupport.c
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Features/Rst/RstUefiDriverSupport/RstUefiDriverSupport.inf
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Include/Protocol/RstLegacyBootDisabledProtocol.h
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/PlatformPkg.dec
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/PlatformPkg.dsc
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/PlatformPkg.fdf
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 36798d89a3ff0b94355ad6252b3c7635b6e23436 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  ICL-U Hynix S3 test fail , cause by VREF_CA abnormality level
  Issue:
  Memory failure after S3 resume.
  Root cause:
  The problem happen @ VREF_CA go low below than CKE may cause DRAM S3 exit command to DRAM.
  This happens because in DdrioInit we enable CA Vref drive from CPU with lowest setting instead of middle range.
  Solution:
  Initialize the VREF CA to middle range value during DdrioInit, to match the board voltage divider.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcMcConfiguration.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: f8a4eb6abb7e3fbadd735e5b80c76725f7080091 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL U][DDR4] MRC fails in 3200G2 in Read Voltage Centering training when dram is in CH1 only
  Issue:
  Certain DDR4 DRAMs (Samsung_2667_2R and Micron_3200_2R) fail in Read Voltage Centering or Early Write Timing Centering 2D.
  Root cause:
  DDR4 "Early ReadMPR Timing Centering 2D" does not fail in range [-31:31] of DqsDelay so the center is 0.
  If we sweep in the full G2 PI range [-62..62], then we start seeing failures, and centering is more precise.
  Solution:
  Double the DqsDelay range in ReadMpr for DDR4 G2.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/ReadTraining/MrcReadDqDqs.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcCommon.c
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Commit: e395eccc12ca60d5a3458f5d1ecb803cb70cf8a3 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg]

  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/CapsuleUpdate: Modify capsule creation scripts to support multiple capsule targets
  This change supports building Monolithic/BIOS/ME/EC Capsules via capsulebuild.bat according to user input.
  (Original capsulebuild.bat only supports building Monolithic and BIOS FMP Capsules)
  1. Move all capsule relative scripts to IceLakePlatSamplePkg\Features\CapsuleUpdate\Tools
  2. Extract the scripts of generating BIOS update images (ClientBios_Ft.rom, BiosUpdate.ini, and BiosBgup.bin) which are required payloads for Monolithic/BIOS FMP Capsule from capsulebuild.bat to IceLakePlatSamplePkg\Features\CapsuleUpdate\Tools\GenBiosUpdateImages\GenBiosUpdateImages.bat
  3. Add scripts to parse BIOS/EC version from BIOS/EC images.
  4. Remove "-bios" argument from capsulebuild.bat. The file name of BIOS ROM must be ClientBios.rom
  5. Remove "rlsrom" argument from capsulebuild.bat. The script will determine if ClientBios.rom is a release build or debug build by parsing the image.
  6. Add "-mever" argument to capsulebuild.bat. User needs to provide ME build version to build a standalone ME Capsule manually.
  Build steps in new capsulebuild.bat becomes:
  1. Determine the capsule build target (monolithic/bios/me/ec capsules) from input arguments
  2. Check binary according to the build target, get BIOS/EC version by invoking GetBiosIdFromBin.py/GetEcVerFromBin.py
  3. Generate BIOS update images by invoking GenBiosUpdateImages.bat
  4. According to capsule build target, generate FMP Capsules by invoking GenCapsuleSysFwBios.bat\GenCapsuleSysFwEc.bat\GenCapsuleSysFwMe.bat\GenCapsuleSysFwMonolithic.bat
  5. The capsules are generated in CapsuleUpdateConfig\CapsuleOutput directory

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 1048ac534e41004ee4a3b6355fe891b4e48becb5 
*********************************************************************************


  BpCommonPkg/HddPassword/Smm: [CVE-2017-5753] Fix bounds check bypass
  Speculative execution is used by processor to avoid having to wait for
  data to arrive from memory, or for previous operations to finish, the
  processor may speculate as to what will be executed.
  If the speculation is incorrect, the speculatively executed instructions
  might leave hints such as which memory locations have been brought into
  cache. Malicious actors can use the bounds check bypass method (code
  gadgets with controlled external inputs) to infer data values that have
  been used in speculative operations to reveal secrets which should not
  otherwise be accessed.
  This commit will focus on the SMI handler(s) registered within the
  HddPassword\Smm driver and insert InternalAsmLfence API to mitigate the
  bounds check bypass issue.
  For SMI handler SmmHddPasswordHandler():
  Code:
  "Port     = ((EFI_HDD_DEVICE_LIST*)(SmmFunctionHeader->Data))->Port;"
  can be a potential cross boundary access of the 'CommBuffer' (controlled
  external inputs) during speculative execution. This cross boundary access
  'Port' can then be passed as parameter 'Identifier' into function
  AtaCmdDispatcher().
  Witin function AtaCmdDispatcher(), 'Port' is used as the index to access
  buffer 'mIdeRegisters'. One can observe which part of the content within
  array was brought into cache to possibly reveal the value of 'Port'.
  Hence, this commit adds an InternalAsmLfence() call after the
  boundary/range checks of 'CommBuffer' to prevent the speculative
  execution.
  A more detailed explanation of the purpose of commit is under the
  'Bounds check bypass mitigation' section of the below link:
  And the document at:
  
  
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword/Smm/HddPasswordSmm.c
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword/Smm/HddPasswordSmm.h
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword/Smm/HddPasswordSmm.inf
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword/Smm/Ia32/Lfence.nasm
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/HddPassword/Smm/X64/Lfence.nasm
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Potential Errors Below:

  --Commit Message Contains Key Word: bypass
  --Commit Message Contains Key Word: internal

*********************************************************************************
Commit: a64ea59fc5b7f133bab3aa2789e4ed47abdd19fe 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg], [MRC]

  [ICL MRC][Fix upper tCWL limit in BIOS Setup for LP4-4267]
  Issue:
  BIOS hits ASSERT when running LP4-4267:
  VarCheckHiiQuestion fail: Numeric mismatch (0x23)
  00000000: 07 08 10 00 01 00 00 22-                         *......."*
  Variable Check handler fail Security Violation - 72C5E28C-7783-43A1-8767-FAD73FCCAFA4:SaSetup
  Root cause:
  Setup code limits tCWL to 34, while in LP4-4267 it is 35.
  Solution:
  Update tCWL Setup limit to 35
  Additional changes:
  - Add an ASSERT in GetSet code to protect against code bugs where a comma is missing in GetSet strings array.
  - Support USER_PROFILE with custom Ratio in LPDDR4: when locking at 1067, use ratio 8 instead of the custom ratio.
  
  
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Setup/OverClockSetup.hfr
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/Include/MrcCommonTypes.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Hal/MrcHalRegisterAccess.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 40734c529112e537bcddd49b8e3a46c0ec605e63 
*********************************************************************************


  BpCommonPkg/WifiConnectionManagerDxe: Fix WCM hang issue in browsers who support
  more than one forms being activated simultaneously
  * V2 Change a typo in commit title
  * Current WCM assumes that user operates step by step, but this assumption is not
  correct. Some browsers support more than one forms being activated simultaneously.
  Like AMI Bios will activate all Forms when entering Bios Setup, that will trigger
  ASSERT in WCM Config Access Callback since no profile are selected at that time.
  This patch is to fix this issue.

[SA], [MRC]

  [ICL MRC][Use CPU TimeStampCounter instead of HPET for MrcWait]
  Change MrcWait routine to use CPU TSC instead of PCH HPET.
  This allows better precision and avoids issue with HPET frequency change in a new PCH generation.
  MrcWait argument is the required delay in nanoseconds.
  Move the MrcWait implementation from MRC core into OEM wrapper layer, for better portability.
  Remove RTC date/time read - it is not used in MRC.

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 19b4f069da94b1bac036d8bfc476d3964a2d2b7a 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL MRC][Add missing IDP registers to Save/Restore table]
  Issue:
  MARS feature is not enabled on C0 stepping after Warm / Fast MRC flow.
  Root cause:
  MARS is enabled in MC Config step, which is skipped in non-Cold flows, but the relevant IDP registers were not part of Save/Restore table.
  Solution:
  Added the following register to Save/Restore table:
  - CCF_IDP_CHANNEL_HASH
  - CCF_IDP_CHANNEL_EHASH
  - CCF_IDP_MAD_INTER_CHANNEL
  - CCF_IDP_MAD_INTRA_CH0
  - CCF_IDP_MAD_INTRA_CH1
  - CCF_IDP_MAD_DIMM_CH0
  - CCF_IDP_MAD_DIMM_CH1
  - CCF_IDP_MARS_ENABLE
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/Include/MrcInterface.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcSaveRestore.c

Commit: a3454d8b7be9e5d8be4290bbdcf46cb931ddac7b 
*********************************************************************************


  Fix-222659:DELL WK717 KB not working after pressing menu in shell.efi
  In DELL WK717keyboard the Array part prefix with a Padding byte. Because
  of this extra padding byte the Old buffer value which is used to Enqueue
  the release key is not happening. THis is because the old buffer is
  always filled with 0x00 padding byte for comparison. This patch fixes
  this problem

Commit: 0dabc72b4cc73bca2cabb83642db9192a5ae668d 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [HSD-ES][client_platf][bug][1606737567][ICL-U/UN][System booting time getting delayed, due to MRC looping between PC: dd6d and DD35]
  1. Change HPET frequency to match actual ICL PCH HPET value.
  2. LPDDR4 training time optimizations:
  - Divide Data stress loopcount by 2 to account for twice longer burst length, which results in the same amount of data UI's as DDR4 at the same loopcount.
  - Divide CMD stress loopcount by 8, to account for CA Victim/Aggressor rotation and "no deselect" sub-tests, so that the total RunIOTest loopcount is as expected.
  - Change ReadMPR PI step from 1 to 2 in the second MrcEarlyReadMprTimingCentering2D (post-ECT), to match the first one.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcApi.h

*********************************************************************************
Commit: c8dd9174dc479c32d9b3e19daab2e5ecd97b2224 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [HSD-ES][client_platf][bug][2205395840][ICL MRC][DataControl2.ForceBiasOn is set on DDR4]
  Issue:
  DataControl2.ForceBiasOn is set on DDR4, this causes extra power consumption.
  It is set in the beginning of JWL FlyBy and not cleared at the end.
  Solution:
  Program ForceBiasOn at the end of JWL FlyBy step according to EV recommendation:
  - Enable ForceBiasOn for QCLK above 1333; otherwise disable.
  - Set the initial Icomp to 9, for all gears / speeds / DDR types
  Additional change:
  - clean up old DDR3/4 ECT code that is never used.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcCommandTraining.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcMcConfiguration.c

Commit: 3bf696d7a0869a6b5875a46ceb2d02c960de921e 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [HSD-ES][client_platf][bug][1407982590][][ICL MRC][Update DDR4 timings per latest JEDEC Spec JESD79-4C Jun 2018]
  Update DDR4 timings per latest JEDEC Spec JESD79-4C Jun 2018.
  1. tDLLK for 2667 and above should be 1024 nCK
  2. Support tCL = [23..32]
  3. Support WR (Write Recovery) of 22 and 26, together with tRTP = 11 and 13.
  Additional change:
  - Remove do_ZQCL from MRS_FSM_CONTROL.
  - LP4: keep high current VRCG mode at the end of MRC; MC will clear it at the end of each SAGV transition because of MrsFsmControl.Clear_VRCG.
  - Refactor DDR4 MR programming routines to have per-DIMM loop for consistency.
  - Remove DDR4 MR dump from MrcPreTraining(), we already print them in Jedec Reset step.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcGeneral.c

[MRC]

  HSD[1305952815] 3 strike while running DDR4 2 ranks dimms
  
  Support new CPUID for ICL B4 stepping:
  - C0 CPUID changed from 0x706E2 to 0x706E3
  - B4 CPUID added: 0x706E2
  
  Updating all Bx stepping checks to include the new B4 CPUID.

[PlatformPkg], [CPU]

  [ICL] Enable PC10 by-default for B4 and C0 parts in BIOS
  With C state set as AUTO from BOIS , the following flow is implemented
  For ICL -U/Y,  (B0/B1/B2/B4/C0)stepping -> PC10
  For ICL UN/YN, for any stepping(B0/B1/B2/B4/C0) its PC8
  
  
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Library/PeiPolicyDebugLib/PeiCpuPolicyDebugLib.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 61d5259f21409a894a4f9ddef9c540def0391bfe 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg], [PCH]

  [PCH] Add support for customer DLL tuning for SD and eMMC
  This new BIOS feature allows customer to provide
  the BIOS with DLL values for SD and eMMC tuned specifically
  for their platform. To support this RC exposes a set of new policies
  typedef struct {
  UINT32  TxCmdDelayControl;
  UINT32  TxDataDelayControl1;
  UINT32  TxDataDelayControl2;
  UINT32  RxCmdDataDelayControl1;
  UINT32  RxCmdDataDelayControl2;
  UINT32  RxStrobeDelayControl;
  } SCS_SD_DLL;
  That allow customer to provide their custom values to be programed instead of
  BIOS defaults. Customer is supposed to fill all DLL values with valid values(selective tuning is not supported)
  and set the UseTunedDlls flag in SDCARD/EMMC config. This new interface supersedes
  old tuning interface for eMMC(HS400 tuning policies) and SD card.
  To accomodate this new interface eMMC software tuning module has been separated from
  PEI initialization module policies. New structure SCS_EMMC_SOFTWRE_TUNING_RESULTS has
  been added to SCS_EMMC_DXE_CONFIG to provide previous tuning results to the software
  tuning module. For S3 resume case boot script that will program the software tuned DLLs
  has been added.
  
  
  IceLakeFspPkg/Library/PeiPolicyUpdateLib/PeiPchPolicyUpdate.c
  IceLakeFspPkg/Upd/FspsUpd.dsc
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Features/EmmcSoftwareTuningStorage/EmmcSoftwareTuningStorage.c
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Include/ScsEmmcSoftwareTuningVariable.h
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Library/DxePolicyUpdateLib/DxePchPolicyUpdate.c
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Library/PeiPolicyUpdateLib/PeiPchPolicyUpdate.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Include/ConfigBlock/ScsConfig.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Include/Protocol/ScsEmmcSoftwareTuning.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Library/DxePchPolicyLib/DxePchPolicyLib.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Library/PeiPchPolicyLib/PchPrintPolicy.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Library/Private/PeiScsLib/PeiScsInitInternal.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Library/Private/PeiScsLib/PeiScsSdHc.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 3573176c7a50d4f825e2f1cc685fda1952f5b618 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg], [SA], [MRC]

  Package/Module: [ICL MRC] "Read Voltage Centering" training showing weird margins at G2
  Add new Training Step Sense Amplifier Correction
  MrcSenseAmpOffsetCorrection algorithm:
  1. Get Rx Vref range for margining.
  2. Perform full Rx Vref range sweep and collect Error Bit mask for each Vref.
  3. Find a biggest Pass region for each bit.
  4. Calculate the Vref center for each bit and average Vref per byte.
  5. Calculate offset that will be added to original senseamp value in order to bring a Vref center of each bit as close as possible to average Vref of whole byte.
  6. Set new Senseamp offset value.
  Add New Bios Setup menu Item "Sense Amplifier Correction" to control the Training.
  Fix DCC Oposit messages in Setup.
  
  
  IceLakeFspPkg/Library/PeiPolicyUpdatePreMemLib/PeiSaPolicyUpdatePreMem.c
  IceLakeFspPkg/Upd/FspmUpd.dsc
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Include/SetupVariable.h
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Library/PeiPolicyUpdateLib/PeiSaPolicyUpdatePreMem.c
  IceLakePlatSamplePkg/Setup/SaSetup.hfr

*********************************************************************************
Commit: e4cc5e462ecf3297db142760a3743abc87d4446c 
*********************************************************************************

[PCH], [ASL]

  Disable OCP timeout for SD and eMMC on D0 transition
  On some platforms it has been observed that transactions
  to SD and eMMC are being dropped due to exceeding OCP timeout.
  Since the expiery of this timeout doesn't generate any interrupt
  software can't react in any way to this and drivers end up waiting
  for a very long time for transaction to finish. The work around for
  this issue is to disable timeout on OCP fabric altogether since there
  are other mechanisms that guard against infinite waits. Disabling OCP
  timeout has to be done on every D0 entry since register responsible for
  that doesn't survive D3 power gated state.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/AcpiTables/Dsdt/PchScs.asl
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Include/Register/PchRegsScsSd.h
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

  --Commit Message Contains Key Word: work around

*********************************************************************************
Commit: dd28802afab7929c2a54de5e7c954d860fcb345e 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg], [PCH]

  [PCH] Integrate core eMMC driver
  This commit introduces core eMMC driver to client platform
  project. To switch from old platform driver to new core driver
  we had to rework the eMMC HS400 tuning which had a dependency on
  the BlockIo protocol installed by the old driver and fix a couple of
  issues in the core driver.
  Changes done to the core driver:
  1. Fix the HS400 switch sequence. Core driver has a wrong HS400 switch sequence
  in which it will try to execute SEND_STATUS while link is at wrong frequency in
  High speed timing. This will result in no response from card.
  2. Introduce eMMC driver strength selection protocol which allows platform code
  to pass desired driver strength to the driver.
  Changes done to the HS400 software tunign:
  1. Software tuning is now disabled by default since it isn't neccessary
  for correct eMMC operation at HS400.
  2. Software tuning module doesn't depend on the platform-provided BlockIo
  protocol anymore. Instead it uses it's own code to access eMMC. This is to ensure
  that OEM can opt to integrate the eMMC driver if boot from eMMC isn't desired. Integration
  of the eMMC driver is also made easier by this change.
  
  
  IceLakeFspPkg/Library/PeiPolicyUpdateLib/PeiPchPolicyUpdate.c

[MRC]

  [ICL MRC]PMO: ICL-U 3200 2Rx8 16GB So-DIMM function test fail , or not boot
  Issue: Certain DDR4 dual rank Micron or Hynix memory won't boot.
  Change: MrcReadLevelingTraining() - remove old CNL W/A for [cnl-u22-c0][SPID rank FIFO overflow]
  which was aligning RxDqFifoRdEnRank to be the same for all ranks, and compensating with Roundtrip which was broken in Gear2.
  This bug is fixed in ICL so no W/A is needed.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/ReadTraining/MrcReadReceiveEnable.c

Commit: c0e603da3c1e1a60adc9c07e35fbc218ffae6db7 
*********************************************************************************

[PCH]

  [PCH] Clear UHS II features support in SD card capabilities bypass
  Our integrated SD card controller advertises support for UHS II
  features by default which is not actually true and might cause
  undefined driver behavior. To prevent that BIOS will clear support
  for such unsupported features.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Library/Private/PeiScsLib/PeiScsSdHc.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: bfde36b5cac314cb01234c8ae67d99af95469497 
*********************************************************************************

[AMT]

  Fix memory and file handles leaks in USB provisioning
  Several of the global memory buffers were not freed after
  provisioning is done and file handle to USB root directory
  has not been closed. This change introduces simpler USB provision
  flow which eliminates all leaks and removes deprecated code(such as
  USB provision header which is not used by MEBx). 3 step flow:
  1. get provision record
  2. remove record
  3. restore record after MEBx invocation if needed
  has been replaced with 2 step flow:
  1. get record
  2. remove record if needed after MEBx invocation.
  To simplify resource management and reduce IO operations.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Amt/BiosExtensionLoader/Dxe/BiosExtensionLoader.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Amt/BiosExtensionLoader/Dxe/BiosExtensionLoader.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Amt/BiosExtensionLoader/Dxe/MebxBiosParamsDebugDumpDxe.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Amt/BiosExtensionLoader/Dxe/ProvisionFile.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Amt/BiosExtensionLoader/Dxe/UsbProvision.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Amt/BiosExtensionLoader/Dxe/UsbProvision.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Amt/Include/Protocol/MebxProtocol.h
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 2c08bf172f0b0bb9e3d01b678157a18a3990a761 
*********************************************************************************

[PCH]

  [PCH] HDA Decoupled mode: Playback appears to be in fast fwd mode after S3/S4 with link freq as 6MHz
  BIOS should not touched LFLCS bit as the default value is 0, which mean using Audio PLL to generate 6 MHz clock.
  This will work with MSFT audio bus driver by default.
  Remove TestLowFreqLinkClkSrc option from policy. Based on it low frequecy mode was enabled/disabled.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Library/Private/PeiHdaInitLib/PeiHdaInitLib.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 143df562aea6ec5d511c094f3326173fd606da49 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [HSD-ES][client_platf][bug][1407432119][][ICL MRC][Early Command Training failed with Micron LP4 2x16 DDP parts]
  Issue:
  MRC fails in ECT with Micron MT53B512M32D2NP LP4 parts.
  Root cause:
  CPU RdOdt = 48 was used together with PU_CAL = VDDQ/2.5, and this combination should not be used per JEDEC Spec.
  This change was done during B0 power on, and it worked fine on other LP4 parts.
  Solution:
  LP4:  Change CPU RdOdt from 48 back to 80, as 48 cannot be used with PU_CAL = VDDQ/2.5
  LP4X: Change CPU RdOdt from 48 back to 60, as 48 cannot be used with PU_CAL = VDDQ * 0.6
  Additional changes:
  LP4/X: Move JedecInitDone / RestoreMRs initialization from MrcJedecInitLpddr4() to MrcResetSequence(),
  so that the frequency switch will be shown at the end of the first JEDEC reset.
  LP4/X: Add condition in DCC init to skip frequency switch if ECT is skipped.
  Also keep running HW-based ReadMPR in ERDMPR2D if ECT is skipped.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcGeneral.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/MemoryTypes/MrcLpddr4.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcCommon.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcGears.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Services/MrcReset.c

  BpCommonPkg/WifiConnectionManagerDxe: Remove Auto Connection Feature
  * Since there is no clear use case for WiFi Auto Connection feature,
  but it brings more security risks, remove it from WCM.
  * Remove Add Network module, Manage Network module, and Network
  Priority Setting module.
  * Remove Save Configuration item on connection page, and remove
  Certificate Input item on certificate enrollment page.
  * Remove KMS and Protected Variable module and Admin Password.

  * Renamed some Marcos and Structures to avoid confusion.
  * Change Scan frequency from 60 back to 30.

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 01b29934b3614ece1b1463e1bf326f50c5dbf79a 
*********************************************************************************

[PlatformPkg], [ASL], [PCH], [SA], [TBT]

  [PCH] Unify ACPI device names between Client and Server
  Client and Server UEFI BIOS ASL code uses different names for devices, e.g., PCI0 vs PC00 for PCI devices and XHC vs XHCI for xHCI devices.
  The name difference makes process of merging client BIOS ACPI code changes into server BIOS code more time-consuming and more difficult.
  It also adds a lot of conditionally compiled code that handles just the name differences.
  As a solution the Client ACPI names were changed, PCIx changed to PCxx (where: xx is hexadecimal number 00..FF) and XHC to XHCI.
  
  
  BpCommonPkg/Library/Usb3DebugPortLib/Usb3DebugPortDataTransfer.c
  BpCommonPkg/Library/Usb3DebugPortLib/Usb3DebugPortInitialize.c
  BpCommonPkg/Library/Usb3DebugPortLib/Usb3DebugPortLibDxe.c
  BpCommonPkg/Library/Usb3DebugPortLib/Usb3DebugPortLibDxeIoMmu.c
  BpCommonPkg/Library/Usb3DebugPortLib/Usb3DebugPortLibInternal.h
  BpCommonPkg/Library/Usb3DebugPortLib/Usb3DebugPortLibPei.c
  BpCommonPkg/Library/Usb3DebugPortLib/Usb3DebugPortLibPeiIoMmu.c
  ClientCommonPkg/Override/BpCommonPkg/Library/Usb3DebugPortLib/Usb3DebugPortDataTransfer.c
  ClientCommonPkg/Override/BpCommonPkg/Library/Usb3DebugPortLib/Usb3DebugPortInitialize.c

[PlatformPkg]

  Remove FSP stack swap and use the same stack with boot loader
  Run FSP on the bootloader temporary memory stack and set up a separate FSP stack only after permanent memory is available.
  Adjust the temporary memory map to reduce the FSP reserved size and increate the UEFI wrapper reserved size.
  PcdFspPermanentMemoryStackSize defines how much data to copy from the wrapper temporary memory stack to the newly created FSP permanent memory stack. If PcdFspHeapSizePercentage != 0, set up a separate FSP stack in permanent memory.
  Hsd-es-id: 1504752730

  Original commit hash: 629dc5e830356668befb4178717348d298f8ad5e

[PlatformPkg]

  IceLakePlatSamplePkg: FPRRs are enabled on capsule flow when BIOS Guard is disabled
  FSP-M UPD data referred by UpdatePeiPchPolicy() function is not valid because the PCD PcdFspmUpdDataAddress is not updated after permanent memory is installed.
  The incorrect value PcdFspmUpdDataAddress referred in PostMem causes FPRR not being disabled as expected.
  1. Set PcdFspmUpdDataAddress in FspWrapper accordingly after FSP migrates FspmUpdData.
  2. Reduce FspCommonLib invocation in FspWrapper - Use PcdFspmUpdDataAddress rather than GetFspMemoryInitUpdDataPointer () in Platform PostMem policy update libraries.

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 88bf04e55308f8573eae6eb38e6bde0a3d164831 
*********************************************************************************


  BpCommonPkg/WifiConnectionManagerDxe: Fixed the error admin password
  is not cleaned in boot time
  * In WiFi connection manager, admin password is used to encrypt/decrypt
  network secrets. To make it more convinient to use, it is designed
  to be kept in memory during the boot time. Such implementation brings
  some security risks which may result admin password leakage. This
  patch fixed this issue, but for sacrifice, user has to input an admin
  password each time he wants to get/set secrets.
  * This patch also fixed the error some passwords and private key files
  are not cleaned before freed.
  * Add a checkbox to indicate if a network should be saved when
  connection triggered.
  * Add some event handlers in EndOfDxe, ExitBootService, and System
  Reset to prevent secrets leakage.
  
  
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/WifiConnectionManagerDxe/Kms/KmsImpl.c
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/WifiConnectionManagerDxe/Kms/VariableEx/VariableEx.c
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/WifiConnectionManagerDxe/WifiConnectionManagerDxe.inf
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/WifiConnectionManagerDxe/WifiConnectionManagerDxe.vfr
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/WifiConnectionManagerDxe/WifiConnectionManagerDxeStrings.uni
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/WifiConnectionManagerDxe/WifiConnectionMgrConfig.h
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/WifiConnectionManagerDxe/WifiConnectionMgrConfigNVDataStruct.h
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/WifiConnectionManagerDxe/WifiConnectionMgrDriver.c
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/WifiConnectionManagerDxe/WifiConnectionMgrDxe.h
  BpCommonPkg/Universal/WifiConnectionManagerDxe/WifiConnectionMgrHiiConfigAccess.c

[PlatformPkg], [SA], [MRC]

  [HSD-ES][client_platf][bug][ICL MRC][Enable Fast MRC by default]
  Enable Fast MRC flow by default.
  Additional changes:
  - Removed MrcTimeMeasure and MrcFastBoot from MEMORY_DXE_CONFIG, they were unused.
  - Moved MrcTimeMeasure from FspmRestrictedConfig to FspmConfig, as it's not a restricted item.
  - Add an error message if memory is TXT-locked at the beginning of MRC, and avoid an endless MRC loop when MC PLL is not locked.
  - Skip SPD hex dump on Warm/S3 flows as we don't read SPD data in these flows.

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 550a26628ffca1fbbe8e88cffdb0414531260d0d 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [ICL B0:Sx fails randomly after n cycles(n=25-800) on LPDDR4 platforms with Mem Initiaization (SAD_ERR_WB_TO_MMIO | CBO/LLC Error  & Cache Hierarchy Error | Cache Hierarchy Error )]
  Issue:
  Memtest fails after MRC sporadically, during Warm / S3 cycling with SAGV enabled.
  Memory reads are corrupted.
  Root cause:
  NORMALMODE_CFG register was part of the MRC save/restore table by mistake.
  Solution:
  This register should not be restored from the table, as it's too early in the flow.
  We go to Normal model in MrcNormalMode() after all 3 SAGV points are restored.
  Additional changes:
  - TcMiniBiosRestricted.bat - build the MiniBios image after MRC version auto-increment.
  - Disable LP4 Tx DqDqs retraining on A-step.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/Include/MrcInterface.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcGeneral.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcSaveRestore.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcStartMemoryConfiguration.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 887bd70162b15e64c885484c28d4d87f4eee90ba 
*********************************************************************************


  ClientCommonPkg: [ICL] Revert current TPM device string assignment.
  Currently the BIOS setup is displaying the current TPM device as "TPM
  2.0 (DTPM)" when using PTT (fTPM).
  The setup form displays the contents on HiiString STR_TCG2_DEVICE_STATE_CONTENT
  as the current TPM device. The current BP implementation defines two cases for
  TPM devices: TPM_DEVICE_1_2 "TPM 1.2" and TPM_DEVICE_2_0_DTPM "TPM 2.0", with the respective strings reflecting the TPM version.
  The ICL implementation overrides some of the BP file to add PTT support. The
  override defines a third case to the HiiString STR_TCG2_DEVICE_STATE_CONTENT
  assignment: TPM_DEVICE_PTT "PTT (fTPM)"; yet this case is never exercised, as
  PTT devices are detected as TPM_DEVICE_2_0_DTPM in the current implementation.
  This change reverts back the HiiString assignment to match the BP
  implementation, displaying "TPM 2.0" for both dTPM and fTPM.
  
  
  ClientCommonPkg/Override/SecurityPkg/Tcg/Tcg2Config/Tcg2ConfigImpl.c
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Potential Errors Below:

  --Commit Message Contains Key Word: revert

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 60b91b9b1054d0042464860aebf2fc92f7e942fd 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [HSD-ES][client_platf][bug][1407122158][][ICL MRC][Memory corruption in LP4-2933]
  Issue:
  At 2933/G2 BIOS fails shortly after MRC, with memory corruption, using LPDDR4.
  Root cause:
  tRDRD_dr turnaround is too tight.
  Solution:
  Include tDQSCK rank-to-rank variance factor into the tRDRD_dr formula, and increase the guardband by 1 tCK.
  Additional changes:
  Control the following features using existing MrcSafeConfig parameter, to quickly isolate failures where MRC passes but full BIOS fails:
  - Relax TAT values
  - Disable CKE power down, Weaklock, Scrambler, periodic temperature reads
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/Include/MrcInterface.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/MemoryInit.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcGeneral.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/McConfiguration/MrcAddressDecodeConfiguration.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/McConfiguration/MrcTimingConfiguration.c

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 433dc7af17c9a9bb4f1a2743450a1dcdfbcbe12e 
*********************************************************************************

[PCH], [ASL]

  [PCH] SD card PWREN# work around
  Integrated SD card controller won't respect
  PWREN# invertion settings when controller is
  put into D3. We work around this by changing
  PWREN# GPIO pad ownership to GPIO controller
  and driving the signal to inactive manually.
  On D3 entry BIOS will reassign GPIO pad ownership
  to SD controller after power gating is disabled.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/AcpiTables/Dsdt/PchScs.asl
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Include/Private/PchConfigHob.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Library/Private/PeiDxeSmmGpioPrivateLib/GpioNativePrivateLib.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/Library/Private/PeiPchInitLib/PchHobs.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Pch/PchInit/Dxe/PchAcpi.c
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

[MRC]

  [HSD-ES][client_platf][bug][1407044790][][ICL MRC][Add missing registers to Save/Restore table]
  1. Add missing registers to Save/Restore table:
  - LP4 DeswizzleCh[0:3]RankPair[01:23]Dev[2:3]
  - VrefAdjust3
  - ScPrCntConfig
  - Ddr4Mr6VrefDimm1ValuesCh[0:1]
  - Lpddr4DiscreteMrValues[0:7] - changed on B0 from 32 to 64-bit
  - Remove DELTADQSCOMMON1 as we don't touch it in MRC.
  2. Additional fix in MrcRestoreTrainingValues:
  - Bring DataControl6 register to the CR cache, we set Lp4ForceDqsNOn to zero in DdrioInit, before it's restored from MrcSave, and later program Gear in this register.
  - Bring DdrMiscControl0 register to the CR cache, we set DataClkGateDisAtIdle to 1 in DdrioInit, before it's restored from MrcSave, and later program Gear in this register.

*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  [HSD-ES][client_platf][bug][1305598735][ICL][ICL Increased Latency Compared to KBL]
  Update Roundtrip Latency optimization step for ICL and enable it for DDR4 only.
  Add support for Gear2.
  When we change Roundtrip, we compensate with the following:
  - READCFGCHx.tCL4RxDqFifoRdEn (tCK) - per SubCh
  - RXDQFIFORDENCHACHBx.RxDqFifoRdEnRank0ChADel (UI) - per SubCh / Rank
  Additional change:
  - Move the common part of RxFifoFlyby (Subch/Rank) into RxFifo (Subch), at the end of Read Leveling.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcStartMemoryConfiguration.c

[PlatformPkg], [CPU]

  [CPU] ICL BIOS OC: Overclocking high voltage mode support through CPU soft strap
  This change adds support for 2 new CPU strap bits: NonCoreHighVoltageMode and CoreHighVoltageMode.
  These CPU straps will be used when doing LN2 cooling to mitigate the CPU cold boot issue historically seen when the CPU reaches very low temperatures.

  Resolution: https://hsdes.intel.com/appstore/article/#/2201923238 Simics doesn't support IA32_SMBASE MSR 0x9E
  	SIMICS HSD 2201923238 implemented IA32_SMBASE_MSR support in SIMICs and there fore the WA added in ICL BIOS is not needed anymore.
  	The WA added was to skip using IA32_SMBASE_MSR in case of SIMIC boot.
  	Now, removing this WA which is no more needed.
  Impacted Platform: ICL
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Cpu/Library/SmmCpuFeaturesLib/SmmCpuFeaturesLib.c
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Potential Errors Below:

  --Commit Message Contains Key Word: bypass

[MRC]

  [ICL-U A2 - Low DDR Memory BW in G1 2R]
  Issue:
  Low memory BW in G1 when ddr4_1dpc feature is enabled.
  Solution:
  Disable Xarb bubble generator on A-step, due to known MC bug:
  [HSD-ES][heia_soc][bugeco][icl-u-b0][1305244232][MC - bubbleGen uses inverted CS for DDR4 bubble]
  XARB_CFG_BUBBLE_INJ.bubble_inj_enable_any_cas_switch = 0
  XARB_CFG_BUBBLE_INJ.bubble_inj_enable_write_switch = 0
  XARB_CFG_BUBBLE_INJ.bubble_inj_enable_read_switch = 0
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Include/MrcVersion.h

*********************************************************************************
Commit: 13e711536ff7917952d29f23c252eed481da5b35 
*********************************************************************************

[MRC]

  IceLakeSiliconPkg: [ICL MRC] MRC Interpreter new commands and improvments
  Issues:
  1.  Exit command does not work properly (does not continue execution)
  2.  When Sagv Enabled - Interpreter commands (step,execute ...) does not work properly.
  Change:
  1. Fix commands execution when Sagv enabled
  2. On "Exit" command the Interpreter will execute all the remaining MRC steps that were not executed and exit to Bios/Minibios.
  3. The command "Exe2pc" renamed to "Goto", a new optional parameter SaGv is added to the command (see help of interpreter).
  4. A new command "c" (continue) is added - the command will execute all remaining command in the table and return to Interpreter loop.
  5. if the Mrc training is done the all execution commands such as Step,Execute.Goto.. are blocked, only non training commands are allowed.
  6. update MrcInterpreter.docx
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/Include/MrcInterface.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/MemoryInit.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Api/MrcStartMemoryConfiguration.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/LibraryPrivate/PeiMemoryInitLib/Source/Include/MrcVersion.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/MemoryInit/MiniBios/MEMORY/MrcSetup.c

  Description: DPC_WATCHDOG_VIOLATION BSOD on GT0 parts with internal Display when Core C-State enable.
  Resolution: Program MSR 0x118 BIT0 to force keep GT0 in RC6.
  Platform Affected: ICL
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/Cpu/Include/CpuRegs.h
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/SaInit/Smm/SaLateInitSmm.c
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/SaInit/Smm/SaLateInitSmm.inf
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Potential Errors Below:

  --Commit Message Contains Key Word: internal

*********************************************************************************
Commit: cba7702c7cadb3a006229b18618d9f6bbb8dca30 
*********************************************************************************

[SA], [ASL]

  [TCSS] TCSS D3 Cold - add on - add MCTP drop hint.
  BIOS program IOP MCTPDrop during D3Cold entry
  (set before IOM D3Cold configuration) and exit (clear after IOM D3Cold configuration and acknowledgement).
  Stepping check needs to be added since this is impacted only in B0 onward.
  
  
  IceLakeSiliconPkg/SystemAgent/AcpiTables/TcssSsdt/TcssSsdt.asl
  

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Potential Errors Below:

  --Commit Message Contains Key Word: stepping

Commit: babac3fd0caa7dcc4a0d62cf39dbc10a8610ed67

  Title:[ICL][Camera]Control logic Device HWID change
  Change the Control logic device HWID from INT3472 to INT346F since CNL platform.
